# Emotion Detection App

This project is a text-based emotion detection web application that predicts human emotions from user input using machine learning and deep learning models.

The goal of this project is to understand how natural language processing (NLP) can be applied to real-world problems and to build a simple, interactive system around it.

---

## Overview

Emotion detection from text plays an important role in applications such as mental health monitoring, chatbots, and user behavior analysis.

In this project, I built a system that:
- Accepts text input from the user  
- Cleans and preprocesses the text  
- Converts it into numerical features using TF-IDF  
- Uses trained models to predict the most likely emotion  

The application is implemented using Streamlit and runs locally for quick interaction.

---

## Features

- Real-time emotion prediction  
- Supports both machine learning and deep learning approaches  
- Simple and easy-to-use interface  
- Efficient text preprocessing using NLP techniques  
- Fast and lightweight setup  

---

## Tech Stack

- Python  
- Streamlit  
- Scikit-learn  
- TensorFlow / Keras  
- NLTK  

---

## Project Structure

- `app.py` → Streamlit interface  
- `main.py` → Core prediction logic  
- `model.h5` → Deep learning model  
- `logistic_regresion.pkl` → Machine learning model  
- `tfidf_vectorizer.pkl` → Feature extractor  
- `label_encoder.pkl` → Label encoder  
- `requirements.txt` → Project dependencies  
- `train.txt` → Dataset  
- `notebook.ipynb` → Model training notebook  

---

## How to Run

1. Clone the repository  


